<!DOCTYPE document PUBLIC "-//APACHE//DTD Documentation V2.0//EN" "http://forrest.apache.org/dtd/document-v20.dtd">

<document>
  <header>
    <title>templeton/pig </title>
  </header>

  <body>
  <section>
   <title>Description</title>
    <p>Provides a Web API for running Pig programs.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
   <title>Usage</title>
    <p><code>POST /v1/templeton/pig.json?src="</code>program.pig<code>"</code></p>
  </section>

  <section>
   <title>Parameters</title>
    <table>
    <tr><th>Name</th><th>Description</th><th>Required?</th><th>Default</th></tr>
    
    <tr><td><strong>exec</strong></td>
        <td>String containing an entire, short pig program to run.</td>
        <td>One of either "exec" or "src" is required</td>
        <td>None</td>
    </tr>
        
    <tr><td><strong>src</strong></td>
        <td>HDFS file name of a pig program to run.</td>
        <td>One of either "exec" or "src" is required</td>
        <td>None</td>
    </tr>  
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
   <title>Results</title>
     <p>The pig resource queues your pig job and returns the JSON object:</p>
     <p><code> {"result": MESSAGE, "jobid": JOBID} </code></p>
     <p>Where MESSAGE is a string similar to "ok", 
        and JOBID is a string containing the ID of your 
        job in the queue.</p>    
  </section> 
  </body>
</document>
